  "texts": [
    "Several observations can be made.",
    "First, all main components in APP-DGNN contribute to the prediction performance of the two sub-tasks: classification of Pass/Fail and Pass/Withdrawn.",
    "Second, APP-IGCN is the model without an IGCN module, which ignores interaction information between learning behavior data and can cause significant degradation in prediction performance.",
    "APP-IGCN shows the worst prediction performance for both sub-tasks, achieving 81.66% and 88.05% for Pass/Fail and Pass/Withdrawn, respectively.Third, both SPP-GCN and APP-DGNN have a temporal modeling process in their models, but APP-DGNN shows better prediction performance than SPP-GCN for both subtasks.",
    "The difference is that the proposed IGCN module in APP-DGNN uses a novel filtering information aggregation design, while SPP-GCN uses a conventional implementation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}